  "prompt": "How did Vodafone get its name?",
  "response": "Vodafone, a prominent telecommunications company, got its name by combining elements from the words **Voice**, **Data**, and **Phone**. The name reflects the company's focus on providing voice and data services over phone networks. It was chosen to represent the company's vision of delivering advanced communication technologies.\n\nThe name \"Vodafone\" was introduced in 1982, when the company rebranded from its original name, **Racal Telecom**, which was a subsidiary of Racal Electronics. Racal Telecom won a license to operate a mobile network in the UK in 1982, and the name change was part of its transition into a dedicated telecommunications provider. The rebranding helped establish Vodafone as a global player in the mobile communications industry.",
